# Echothink-Patch: 0006-login-gate
# Title: Enforce local login-required startup/navigation gate
# Area: login-gate, startup, navigation
# Depends-On: echothink/0011-first-run-gate-shell.patch (T11 makes chrome://echothink-first-run the sole first-run tab; this patch keeps that local shell as the blocked-navigation recovery page after first run)
# Spec-Depends-On: docs/echothink-browser-alpha/t20-define-login-gate-local-state-and-allowlist.md (T20 defines the readiness prefs, exact unauthenticated allowlist, blocked-navigation behavior, setup completion, and reset/logout semantics)
# Browser-Layer-Reason: The browser must prevent normal top-level browsing before local auth/device setup is complete, including typed URLs, startup/restored tabs, New Tab, and browser-created popup/window navigations. This is a browser-shell startup/navigation decision that must work before any Echothink backend is reachable; backend services still own server-side auth, device authorization, replay protection, and rollout policy.
# Preferred-Surface-Checked: preferences, existing-hook, narrow-native-navigation (profile prefs hold only non-secret readiness flags; New Tab uses the existing URL rewrite hook; browser-level navigations use NavigateParams before app/window routing)
# Security-Critical-Areas: none (no network stack, TLS validation, sandbox, renderer internals, downloads, history, bookmarks, password manager, cookies, or DevTools changes)
# Native-Files-Touched: chrome/browser/chrome_content_browser_client.cc, chrome/browser/ui/browser_navigator.cc
# Rebase-Risk: medium (touches the New Tab URL handler and desktop NavigateParams path used by existing Echothink New Tab and echo-route patches)
# Validation: Apply inherited patches and active Echothink predecessors through echothink/0011-first-run-gate-shell.patch, then this patch with `patch -p1` against pinned Chromium 148.0.7778.178. Build and verify with a fresh normal profile: (1) first launch opens chrome://echothink-first-run; (2) chrome://newtab resolves to chrome://echothink-first-run until readiness prefs are true; (3) typed arbitrary HTTPS URLs rewrite to chrome://echothink-first-run before setup; (4) the explicit T20 auth/enrollment/support/update/diagnostic routes remain reachable; (5) setting echothink.auth.session_ready, echothink.device.enrolled, and echothink.device.verified true restores normal navigation.
#
# Notes:
# - This patch stores only non-secret readiness booleans and empty diagnostic
#   strings. It never stores access tokens, refresh tokens, private key material,
#   request proofs, full blocked URLs, queries, fragments, or referrers.
# - `echothink.setup.complete` is treated as a derived cached boolean. The gate
#   recomputes it from `echothink.auth.session_ready`,
#   `echothink.device.enrolled`, and `echothink.device.verified`; if any
#   underlying readiness flag is false, the cached setup-complete flag is
#   cleared.
# - Blocked browser-level navigations are rewritten to
#   chrome://echothink-first-run and the referrer is cleared. The blocked target
#   is not appended to the local URL or persisted.
# - The allowlist exactly follows the T20 spec for setup, diagnostics, update,
#   support, and browser-required routes. General app/workspace routes, external
#   sites, direct IP literals, file://, arbitrary extension URLs, and external
#   protocol handlers are not allowed before setup.
# - This is not backend authorization. Echothink services and gateways remain
#   responsible for session validity, device authorization, replay protection,
#   and protected workspace/business data.

--- a/chrome/browser/chrome_content_browser_client.cc
+++ b/chrome/browser/chrome_content_browser_client.cc
@@ -608,5 +608,41 @@ GURL ReplaceURLHostAndPath(const GURL& url,
       url::Component(0, path.length()));
   return url.ReplaceComponents(replacements);
 }
